Texts.Chs:
不管怎样，我们还没有谈到好的方面。看看这个。

 ^yellow;[奇怪的咯吱声]^reset;

你现在看到的是...嗯，其实我也不知道。它就像某种胶袋，已经取代了胃。从内部我设法提取了一些... 有趣的东西。

Texts.Eng:
Anyhow, we aren't even getting to the good stuff yet. Check this out. 

 ^yellow;[ Strange squishing sounds ]^reset;

 What you are seeing here is...well, I actually have no idea. It's like some sort of gel-sack that has taken the place of a stomache. From within I managed to extract some...interesting things.

Texts.Chs:
这个实验对象几乎没有可见的表皮，因为他的整个身体被包裹在一种外骨骼中，看起来像是由锯齿状的骨头组成的。

^yellow;[一个声音问: “他怎么能长出这样的新骨头？这说不通啊。这些电线是怎么回事？”]^reset;

 合理的问题。 我怀疑骨头的问题就像进行性骨化性纤维发育不良。其他的... 我还是一无所知。

Texts.Eng:
The subject has nearly no visible epidermis of his own, as his entire body is encased in a sort of exoskeleton that appears to be composed of jagged bone.

^yellow;[ a voice asks 'How could he just grow new bone like this? It doesn't make sense. And what the hell is up with all this wire? ]^reset;

 Valid questions. I suspect the bone issue is like Fibrodysplasia ossificans progressiva. The rest...I remain clueless.
